In this data set, there are two times listed, when the case was opened and when it was close. For the sake of simplicity, we will only be concerning ourselves when the crime was first reported, because we want to be as close to the time where the crime actually occured We should also go ahead and remove any 'codes' as they won't be super useful when we conduct any analysis

df = df.sort_values(by='Date', ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)
df = df[df['Date'].isna() == False]
df = df[df['Date'] > pd.to_datetime("1/1/2006")]

I also noticed that some of the offense descriptions were somewhat specific, so I added a more general offense column

In [92]:
df['Offense'] = 'Other'

def f(x):
    if x in ['RAPE','LOITERING/DEVIATE SEX','SEX CRIMES','FELONY SEX CRIMES']:
        return 'Sexual Assault and Rape'
    elif x in ['ASSAULT 3 & RELATED OFFENSES','FELONY ASSAULT']:
        return 'Assault'
    elif x in ['KIDNAPPING','KIDNAPPING & RELATED OFFENSES','KIDNAPPING AND RELATED OFFENSES']:
        return 'Kidnapping'
    elif x in ['MURDER & NON-NEGL. MANSLAUGHTER','HOMICIDE-NEGLIGENT,UNCLASSIFIE']:
        return 'Homicide'
    elif x in ['INTOXICATED & IMPAIRED DRIVING','INTOXICATED/IMPAIRED DRIVING','HOMICIDE-NEGLIGENT-VEHICLE']:
        return 'Impaired Driving'
    elif x in ['ROBBERY',"BURGLAR'S TOOLS",'BURGLARY','PETIT LARCENY','PETIT LARCENY OF MOTOR VEHICLE',
               'POSSESSION OF STOLEN PROPERTY','THEFT OF SERVICES','THEFT-FRAUD']:
        return "Robbery and Theft"
    elif x is 'ARSON':
        return 'Arson'
    else:
        return 'Other'


df['Offense'] = df['Offense Description'].apply(f)

df.head()

A most immediate observation is the effect COVID-19 had initially on various crimes. In all metrics except homocide (which seemingly shot up), crime went substantially down.

Something discussed during the begining of the pandemic was the percieved uptick in crime against Asian Americans

These graphs do not really tell much, other than the population density /traffic of each borough. To derive any meaning, we must further cut the data.

Let us first examine the age group of the victime, and see if their is any connection between the location and the crime committed. We will then look at various conditional statistics.

First, we let the built in cluster function in folium cluster our crimes in order to see if we can see some sort of pattern

In [ ]:
m = fl.Map(
    location=[40.730610, -73.935242],
    zoom_start=11
)

cluster = MarkerCluster().add_to(m)

for i,x in df_heatmap.iterrows():
    fl.Marker([x['Latitude'], x['Longitude']]).add_to(cluster)
    
heat = HeatMap(df_heatmap,
                min_opacity=0.2,
                radius=30, blur=20, 
                max_zoom=11)
heat.add_to(m)
m
